<br>
As noted before there is a room beyond the Prasertum quarters in each of the Consillium. It could just be empty space but there is also a door visible in that room. I cannot figure out how to access it.<br>
<br>
There is a set of chairs and a table in another inaccessible place outside of the jail (the one w/o netherbians). <br>
<br>
Both of these things are visible through the sit by the wall trick.<br>
<br>
It's possible to gain access to presumably off limits portions of the map by taking the teleporter by the entrance to Seru up to the outer guard ring. Once you are up there go out the window immediately behind the portal switch and start walking along the ledge. If you follow the ledge around to the arena area you can jump down onto interior walls and eventually access some of the high walls by the Consillium. The walls are too far away to be able to jump onto the side of the Consillium however. You can also jump down into unfinished portions of the map near the arena jail and slip through holes in the mesh. All in all the exploration didn't turn up anything useful for the quest though. It more seems like a side-effect of the way the zone was designed.<br>
<br>
